    "course_title": "SOCIOLOGY OF ECONOMIC INSTITUTIONS",
    "description": "Sociological perspectives on the organization of the firm, financial markets, and work, intermediate associations (unions, ethnic economies), the state, and the international economy. Contrast between neoclassical, traditional institutionalist, post-fordist, and neo-fordist perspectives on the nature and evolution of these institutions.",
